# M15b canary per GPT-5.5 post-impl review: `extern` does NOT
# bypass `pub` cross-module. A private extern with a `pub`
# safe-wrapper is the V1 pattern; calling the extern directly
# from another module must error with the visibility diagnostic
# (not the extern-needs-raw diagnostic). This preserves the
# safe-wrapper contract: outside callers reach `a.safe_puts`,
# never `a.puts` directly.
use a

sub main()
  raw
    a.puts("hi")
